---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import DataEntryApp from '../islands/DataEntryApp.tsx';
---
<BaseLayout title="Add data — Ehvidence" description="Turn a study into a data block.">
  <h1>From a study to a data block</h1>
  <p>
    This tool turns the numbers you read in a paper into a validated data block for the site. Enter
    the topic details and add one card per study — typically the events and group sizes from a 2×2
    table (e.g. <em>5 of 250</em> in the treatment arm, <em>12 of 248</em> in control). The risk
    ratio, confidence interval, percent improvement, and NNT/NNH are computed live with the exact
    same engine that renders the published pages.
  </p>
  <ol class="small">
    <li>Fill in the topic and outcome fields.</li>
    <li>Add studies; for each, paste the 2×2 counts (or a reported RR/OR/HR with its CI).</li>
    <li>Review the live pooled preview and forest plot.</li>
    <li><strong>Email it to the webmaster</strong> for us to add — or, if you contribute directly, <strong>export the JSON</strong>, save it as <code>src/content/topics/&lt;slug&gt;.json</code>, and commit. The topic page builds itself.</li>
  </ol>

  <DataEntryApp client:load />
</BaseLayout>
